Set up and Load Data

First, were going to load our dataset, which includes a list of 13 genes (the Cisplatin Sensitivity Signature) and TCGA expression data for many types of epithelial-based cancers. Lets take a look at our signature. If you wish to perform the analysis yourself, you may uncomment the line manually loading the signature.

cisplatin_sens_sig <- readRDS(here("Cisplatin_Signature.rds"))

Data Pre-Processing

Format Dataframe

Here, were combining all the TCGA samples into a single dataframe, with a column to label their histology in the data frame epi_tcga. Then, well create a new dataframe that contains just 13 columns, containing the gene expression for all TCGA samples, epi_tcga_cis_sig.

epi_tcga <- bind_rows(tcga_BLCA, tcga_BRCA, tcga_CESC, tcga_COAD, tcga_HNSC, 
                      tcga_KIRC, tcga_KIRP, tcga_LIHC, tcga_LUAD, 
                      tcga_LUSC, tcga_OV, tcga_PAAD, tcga_PRAD, tcga_STAD, 
                      tcga_THCA, tcga_UCEC)

epi_tcga_cis_sig <- epi_tcga %>%
  select(all_of(cisplatin_sens_sig))

Now, we need to start formatting these dataframes with the final product in mind. We want a violin plot that ranks the groups in order. For this, well say we want them ranked by median value of the entire group. Well extract these median group values, then convert the tcga_label and tissue variables to ordered factors. ggplot2 will recognize these orders and automatically apply them when plotting. In addition to this, well find the number of samples in each group, which will be used later in plotting.

median_epi_group <- epi_tcga_cis_sig %>%
  group_by(tcga_label, tissue) %>%
  summarize(median = median(median_expr), n = n()) %>%
  arrange(desc(median))
## `summarise()` regrouping output by 'tcga_label' (override with `.groups` argument)
median_epi_group <- median_epi_group %>%
  # ungroup(n) %>%
  # ungroup(tcga_label) %>%
  # ungroup(tissue) %>%
  mutate(tcga_label = fct_reorder(tcga_label, desc(median))) %>%
  mutate(tissue = fct_reorder(tissue, desc(median)))



epi_tcga_cis_sig$tcga_label <- factor(epi_tcga_cis_sig$tcga_label, 
                                      ordered = TRUE, 
                                      levels = median_epi_group$tcga_label)
epi_tcga_cis_sig$tissue <- factor(epi_tcga_cis_sig$tissue, 
                                      ordered = TRUE, 
                                      levels = median_epi_group$tissue)

Finally, we need to plot these scores on a log-scale axis. This means that we cant have any negative or 0 values. Well make a new dataframe, called viol_data with linearly scaled scores. Here, we simply add the minimum value to all the scores and 1. This means that the scores will start at a minimum of 1. Well confirm that thats the case and take a final look at our dataset before plotting.

viol_data <- epi_tcga_cis_sig
viol_data$median_expr <- epi_tcga_cis_sig$median_expr + (abs(min(epi_tcga_cis_sig$median_expr))+1)

Create Violin Plots

Well use viol_data to plot our ordered violin plots. This function requires a dataframe that contains a column with the signature scores (median_expr) and a column labeling each samples histology. Here, thats tcga_label and below we use tissue. The colors are simply for aesthetics, labeling by each subgroup. Finally, we use a second (median_epi_group) dataframe containing some summarized characteristics for each label. We label each violin plot with the total number of samples (n) in each group.

ggplot(viol_data, aes(x = tcga_label, y=median_expr)) +
  geom_violin(trim = FALSE, scale = "width", aes(fill=tissue)) +
  geom_boxplot(width = 0.12, outlier.shape = NA) +
  scale_y_continuous(trans="log10") +
  scale_x_discrete(expand = c(0,0)) +
  geom_label(aes(x = tcga_label, y = .9, label = n), data = median_epi_group,
             label.padding = unit(0.15, "lines")) +
  coord_flip() +
  ylab("Signature Score") + xlab("Cancer Subtype") + 
  theme_bw(base_size = 17) +
  theme(axis.text.y = element_text(angle = 30),
    axis.title=element_text(face="bold"),
        legend.position = "none")

ggplot(viol_data, aes(x = tissue, y=median_expr)) +
  geom_violin(trim = FALSE, scale = "width", aes(fill=tissue)) +
  geom_boxplot(width = 0.12, outlier.shape = NA) +
